t was not too chilly for the boy to go about without his coat, and Anna Petrovna replied that the white sweater he had on was sufficiently thick and comfy. Olga somehow had never much liked Anna Petrovna and her sweet saintliness.

'I want to take him for a good long walk,' said Krug. 'You must have had quite enough of him. Lunch at one, is that right?'

